I wasn&#x27;t sure entirely what you were getting at with const variables in C that are initialized later  and this doesn&#x27;t fit your bill, if you were referring to lazy evaluation  but you can do something like this (apparently works for Clang and GCC):<p><pre><code>    const int test = ({
        int a = 1+1;
        sqrt(a);
    });</code></pre>
